data.content:
Blockchain
Technology proposed to create immutable/transparent contract systems. Prevents data tampering, enables mutual monitoring, and provides investigation evidence for corruption cases.

Corruption
The issue targeted by the blockchain solution within infrastructure projects, combated through preventive and remedial measures to enhance integrity.<SEP>The problem occurring during infrastructure project development cycles, leading to financial losses and safety violations. Specifically involves contract tampering.

Safety Standards
Standards that are violated due to corruption in infrastructure projects, leading to casualties as mentioned in the text.

Contracts
Agreements serving as failsafes (providing verifiable paper trails) but also vulnerabilities when tampered with during project implementation.

Government
The government suffers significant financial losses due to corruption in infrastructure projects according to the text.

Energy Consumption
A pressing issue with blockchain technology mainly attributed to its consensus mechanism, discussed as a challenge requiring solution.

Infrastructure Projects
Construction and development initiatives that the blockchain solution aims to manage, described as the city's structural foundation where corruption occurs.<SEP>Projects forming civilization foundations like highways and hospitals. Vulnerable to corruption during development cycles.

Paper Contracts
Conventional contract formats susceptible to tampering, creating entry points for corruption.

Consensus Mechanism
A component of blockchain technology contributing to its high energy consumption, identified as a problem needing innovation.

Blockchain Solution
A system being developed to manage infrastructure projects through custom blockchain technology, including a proprietary consensus mechanism and core features while removing unnecessary elements.

Proprietary Consensus Mechanism
A custom blockchain component being developed as part of the blockchain solution's implementation plans.

Core Blockchain Characteristics
Fundamental attributes of blockchain technology retained in the solution's design while removing unnecessary elements.
